                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Johnson Electoral Mission/6:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-24T10:00:00-05:45"
                            >May 24, 1930—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Department’s 39, May 8, 7 p.m. The Supreme Court of Nicaragua on May 23 named
                    Captain Alfred Wilkinson Johnson, President of the National Board of
                    Elections.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
